history.content:
The past course websites are here, so I would recommend looking through the readings/notes

https://inst.eecs.berkeley.edu/~ee16b/fa18/

https://sp18.datastructur.es/

children.subject: In addition to reading up on the stuff earlier, make sure you understand all the linear algebra (change of basis, eigenvalues, diagonalization) and circuits stuff (KVL, KCL, op-amp golden rules, capacitors) rock solid from 16a if you want to be successful in 16b. 16b leverages and assumes 16a very heavily. That is actually probably the best preparation.
